h2. Summary
Synchrony has a command line parameter {{ip.whitelist}} which was supposed to provide better security by checking the caller IP against the whitelist. After the fork this parameter became obsolete and doesn't affect business logic at all.

Nevertheless, it still writes warning into the logs if the IP is not matched. We should remove this logging because it is misleading for the customer and for support engineers. 

h2. Log Sample
Log sample can be seen below and is usually found inside Synchrony Log File:
{code}
{"synchrony":{"message":"synchrony.http [warn] Secret request made from outside IP whitelist","ip":"192.31.5.128","ns":"synchrony.http"}}
{"synchrony":{"message":"synchrony.http [warn] Secret request made from outside IP whitelist","ip":"192.31.5.126","ns":"synchrony.http"}}
{code}

h2. Bonus
Remove all things related to {{ip.whitelist}} parameter because it is confusing and adds needless complexity

