h3. Summary

Task report macro not rendering tasks list, whenever spacestatus is null.
This is reported to add constraint on spacestatus value not to accept null value that would cause tast report macro malfunctioning.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create task list on a page
# Create a task report macro to list and select previous created page as a resource for the macro
# on database side, change spacestatus to Null
{code:borderStyle=solid}
update spaces set spacestatus = Null where spaceid = '98306';
{code}

h3. Expected Results
* values of spacestatus should be either (archived or current), there should be constraint added to reject Null values and handle that on the reported logs

h3. Actual Results
* task report render 'looking good, no incomplete tasks'


h3.Workaround
# Stop Confluence
(!) Always take a backup of your database, confluence home and install directories.
# First check the problematice space by below query, make sure that returning SPACESTATUS: NULL
{code:borderStyle=solid}
mysql> select * from SPACES where SPACEKEY = 'test';
{code}
# Then update status to Current status
{code:borderStyle=solid}
update spaces set spacestatus = 'CURRENT' where spaceid = '98306' ;
{code}
# Start confluence
# Then you should be able to render task report macro properly

